<subSubSection id="F95EAAC15663756D0078DCC1C10D82EC" pageId="0" pageNumber="33" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="264C6F60586529B2F101A3B11B3C1392" pageId="0" pageNumber="33">Diagnosis.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="BFC6E7B647EFF66B082F5C926735C5FB" pageId="0" pageNumber="33">
This species can be distinguished from other Afrotropical 
<taxonomicName id="CB7AEC1EDA7B56866C81A4B6A0F4614B" lsidName="" pageId="0" pageNumber="33" rank="subfamily" subfamily="Rhyssinae">Rhyssinae</taxonomicName>
by the combination of lateral carinae on the frons and the absence of a raised flange on the dorsal margin of the mesopleuron. No other species has the same colour pattern.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="C1951B580BDDFC376321E5094252CB28" pageId="0" pageNumber="33">
<emphasis id="FA2B5AF38EA62FA5F0778CE3BACF2186" bold="true" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="33">Head</emphasis>
: frons with median carinae diverging towards ocelli, with lateral carinae curving towards lateral ocelli; hypostomal carina raised into an elevated flange, its height greater than the maximum width of the second maxillary palp segment.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="66C4ED81E2B12AF515D09799E54A9FC7" pageId="0" pageNumber="33">
<emphasis id="85C48588C31B919E30CD5E24CE430BBF" bold="true" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="33">Mesosoma</emphasis>
: subalar prominence without a lateral flange; mesopleuron without a flange along the dorsal margin; epicnemial carina reaches the approximate height of the mesopleural pit.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="E922F1EFE45DD8537E406E85D506085E" pageId="0" pageNumber="33">
<emphasis id="458BEE3D6F64C89BCEC5D72DC90DAC32" bold="true" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="33">Metasoma</emphasis>
: tip of apical horn elliptical in posterior view; tergite 3 mostly smooth.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
